[EHD is the most important disease of white-tailed deer. Outbreaks are common in the southeast USA. According item [3] above, deaths in Michigan are at higher levels than usual, which may be cause for concern.

For more information on this disease, see the moderator comments in ProMED-mail post 20110918.2842. - Mod.PMB]
